  "texts": [
    "Being able to use an explainable AI method then implies that the problem might need to be adapted to the methods currently available, leading to possible losses of information and lower prediction accuracy (State et al., 2022).",
    "Also, interpreting explainability methods requires significant amounts of domain knowledge regarding the application context; a lack of such knowledge might render the explanations meaningless to (lay) end-users.",
    "Integration can be either achieved by involving the respective experts into the evaluation (see Sect.",
    "\"Multi-stakeholder participatory design\"), or by directly integrating it via symbolic approaches (Calegari et al., 2020), or knowledge-informed AI methods (see Sect.",
    "\"Knowledge-informed AI models\")."
  ],
